data.description: Introducing a picturesque mid-century ranch at 423 S Windsor, set in the highly desirable Village neighborhood, where the trees canopy over the streets. Built in 1952, this mid-century architectural beauty spans across 2,198 square foot and has been meticulously cared for, boasting recent upgrades including new interior paint, an upgraded HVAC system, a new main sewer line, 50-gallon water heater, and a new electrical service panel. Step inside to discover bright, spacious interiors complemented by hardwood flooring and neutral colors throughout. Falling in love with the generously proportioned layout is easy, which includes 3 comfortable bedrooms, 2 and a half bathrooms, and a light-filled kitchen with an attractive layout, resin quartz countertops, stainless appliances, and a massive pantry/utility/laundry room. Plus, an open floor plan means the kitchen adjoins the inviting sunroom, expanding your entertaining space. Enjoy the conveniences of a great yard fenced for privacy, an attached 2-car garage, and additional outdoor structures including a shed and patio. Whether you're soaking up the sunset view or enjoying the mid-century stacked limestone fireplace, this property is sure to impress. Listed at $315,000, you won't want to miss out on this opportunity to OWN the home you love!
